        <h2>Your Data, Your Control</h2>
        
        <p>
          At Eventasaurus, we believe that you should have full control over your personal data. This page outlines the comprehensive rights you have regarding your information and how you can exercise those rights within our platform.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Data Subject Rights Under GDPR and CCPA</h2>
        
        <p>
          If you are a resident of the European Union or California, you have specific statutory rights regarding your personal data. Eventasaurus complies with applicable data protection regulations and provides the following rights to all users globally:
        </p>

        <h3>1.1 Right to Access (Article 15 GDPR / CCPA Section 1798.110)</h3>
        <p>
          You have the right to obtain confirmation as to whether or not personal data concerning you is being processed, and where that is the case, access to the personal data and the following information:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>The purposes of the processing</li>
          <li>The categories of personal data concerned</li>
          <li>The recipients or categories of recipients to whom personal data has been or will be disclosed</li>
          <li>Where possible, the envisaged period for which personal data will be stored</li>
          <li>The existence of the right to request rectification or erasure of personal data</li>
          <li>The source of the personal data where it is not collected from the data subject</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>1.2 Right to Rectification (Article 16 GDPR)</h3>
        <p>
          You have the right to obtain from Eventasaurus without undue delay the rectification of inaccurate personal data concerning you. Taking into account the purposes of the processing, you shall have the right to have incomplete personal data completed, including by means of providing a supplementary statement.
        </p>

        <h3>1.3 Right to Erasure - "Right to be Forgotten" (Article 17 GDPR / CCPA Section 1798.105)</h3>
        <p>
          You have the right to obtain from Eventasaurus the erasure of personal data concerning you without undue delay, and we shall have the obligation to erase personal data without undue delay where one of the following grounds applies:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>The personal data are no longer necessary in relation to the purposes for which they were collected</li>
          <li>You withdraw consent on which the processing is based</li>
          <li>You object to the processing and there are no overriding legitimate grounds for the processing</li>
          <li>The personal data have been unlawfully processed</li>
          <li>The personal data must be erased for compliance with a legal obligation</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>1.4 Right to Restriction of Processing (Article 18 GDPR)</h3>
        <p>
          You have the right to obtain from Eventasaurus restriction of processing where one of the following applies:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>The accuracy of the personal data is contested by you</li>
          <li>The processing is unlawful and you oppose the erasure of the personal data</li>
          <li>Eventasaurus no longer needs the personal data for the purposes of the processing</li>
          <li>You have objected to processing pending the verification of whether legitimate grounds override yours</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>1.5 Right to Data Portability (Article 20 GDPR)</h3>
        <p>
          You have the right to receive the personal data concerning you, which you have provided to Eventasaurus, in a structured, commonly used and machine-readable format. You have the right to transmit those data to another controller without hindrance from Eventasaurus, where:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>The processing is based on consent or on a contract</li>
          <li>The processing is carried out by automated means</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>1.6 Right to Object (Article 21 GDPR)</h3>
        <p>
          You have the right to object, on grounds relating to your particular situation, at any time to processing of personal data concerning you which is based on legitimate interests. Eventasaurus shall no longer process the personal data unless we demonstrate compelling legitimate grounds for the processing which override your interests, rights and freedoms.
        </p>

        <h2>2. How to Exercise Your Rights</h2>
        
        <h3>2.1 Account Settings Dashboard</h3>
        <p>
          Many of your data rights can be exercised directly through your Eventasaurus account settings:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Data Download:</strong> Export all your personal data in JSON format</li>
          <li><strong>Account Deletion:</strong> Permanently delete your account and associated data</li>
          <li><strong>Profile Updates:</strong> Modify or correct your personal information</li>
          <li><strong>Privacy Settings:</strong> Control data processing preferences</li>
          <li><strong>Communication Preferences:</strong> Manage marketing and notification settings</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2.2 Data Rights Request Form</h3>
        <p>
          For more complex requests or if you prefer not to use your account dashboard, you can submit a formal data rights request. We will verify your identity and respond within the legally required timeframes (typically 30 days for GDPR requests, 45 days for CCPA requests).
        </p>

        <h3>2.3 Verification Process</h3>
        <p>
          To protect your privacy and security, we may request additional information to verify your identity before processing certain data rights requests. This may include:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Email verification from your registered account</li>
          <li>Additional identifying information for account recovery scenarios</li>
          <li>Government-issued identification for high-security requests</li>
        </ul>

