        <h2>5. Data Processors and Third Parties</h2>
        
        <p>
          Eventasaurus works with the following categories of data processors to provide our services. All processors are bound by Data Processing Agreements (DPAs) that ensure GDPR compliance:
        </p>
        
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Cloud Infrastructure:</strong> Amazon Web Services, Google Cloud Platform</li>
          <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> Anonymized usage analytics providers</li>
          <li><strong>Email Services:</strong> Transactional and marketing email providers</li>
          <li><strong>Payment Processing:</strong> PCI-compliant payment processors (we do not store payment card data)</li>
          <li><strong>Customer Support:</strong> Help desk and live chat platforms</li>
          <li><strong>Security Services:</strong> DDoS protection, security monitoring, fraud prevention</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. International Data Transfers</h2>
        
        <p>
          Eventasaurus operates globally and may transfer your personal data outside your home country. When we transfer data internationally, we ensure appropriate safeguards are in place:
        </p>
        
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Adequacy Decisions:</strong> We transfer data to countries with adequacy decisions from your local data protection authority</li>
          <li><strong>Standard Contractual Clauses:</strong> We use EU Standard Contractual Clauses for transfers to countries without adequacy decisions</li>
          <li><strong>Binding Corporate Rules:</strong> Where applicable, we implement binding corporate rules for intra-group transfers</li>
          <li><strong>Certification Schemes:</strong> We work with providers who maintain relevant privacy certifications</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>7. Automated Decision Making and Profiling</h2>
        
        <p>
          Eventasaurus may use automated decision-making in limited circumstances:
        </p>
        
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Spam Detection:</strong> Automated systems flag potentially spam events or accounts</li>
          <li><strong>Security:</strong> Automated fraud detection and account security measures</li>
          <li><strong>Recommendations:</strong> Event recommendation algorithms based on your preferences</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>
          You have the right not to be subject to a decision based solely on automated processing, including profiling, which produces legal effects concerning you or similarly significantly affects you. If you believe you have been subject to impactful automated decision-making, please contact us.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Data Breach Notification</h2>
        
        <p>
          In the event of a personal data breach that is likely to result in a high risk to your rights and freedoms, Eventasaurus will notify you without undue delay (within 72 hours of becoming aware of the breach, where feasible). We will provide:
        </p>
        
        <ul>
          <li>Description of the nature of the personal data breach</li>
          <li>Categories and approximate number of data subjects concerned</li>
          <li>Likely consequences of the personal data breach</li>
          <li>Measures taken or proposed to address the breach</li>
          <li>Contact information for our Data Protection Officer</li>
        </ul>

